content:
The Salesforce data model is the Digital Insurance Platform of choice. If you use the Vlocity package data model, the process of switching to the Salesforce data model is called harmonization.

To benefit from new and enhanced features in the future, you must move to the Salesforce data model. This involves using new objects and services that integrate seamlessly into the Salesforce Customer 360 platform.

Plan Your Switch to the Salesforce Data Model
Switching to the Salesforce data model ensures you get new and enhanced features for the Digital Insurance Platform in the future. But it's up to you whether to harmonize, and when. It's a large undertaking that requires an analysis of your org, and potentially updates to custom components.

Harmonize existing data and move to the Salesforce data model for:

* Insurance Policies
* Claims
* Group Benefits

Enable or Disable the Insurance Industries Extension Data Model
When you install or upgrade to the Insurance managed package and the Insurance Industries Extension package, use a custom setting to disable the use of the core object model until you're ready to make the switch.

Harmonized LWCs and Services
No special action is required for harmonized LWCs and services to work with your harmonized data.
title: Harmonizing Insurance Org in Salesforce
